Reception at DPRK Embassy in Havana 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- A reception was given at the DPRK embassy in Havana on October 2 on the occasion of the 77th birthday of Fidel Castro Ruz, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Cuba and president of its Council of State and the Council of Ministers.
 Present on invitation were members of the CPC Central Committee and officials of the Department of International Affairs of the party, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the Ministry of the Revolutionary Armed Forces and the Ministry of Internal Affairs. And the DPRK ambassador and embassy officials were present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first vice-minister of Foreign Affairs of Cuba in a speech said that the Cuban and Korean peoples established fraternal and comradely relations long ago and have struggled against U.S. imperialism, the common enemy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have become more arrogant in their moves in recent years to lord it over in the world, he noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under this situation we should staunchly fight against the U.S. imperialists' moves for aggression and maintain the revolutionary principle, rallied close around the party and the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our two peoples will further strengthen the solidarity based on the revolutionary principle in the future, too, as in the past so as to check and frustrate the U.S. imperialists' moves for aggression and achieve a great victory in the socialist construction.

Foreign Diplomats Visit Party Founding Museum 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Officials in charge of cultural and friendly relations of different embassies in Pyongyang Tuesday visited the Party Founding Museum on the occasion of the 6th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 58th anniversary of the WPK.
 They looked round historic relics, being briefed on the fact that President Kim Il Sung founded the WPK after the country's liberation on the basis of the organizational and ideological foundation for the party founding and the revolutionary traditions provided by him in the days of the bloody &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
anti-Japanese struggle and strengthened and developed the party into a strong party rooted among broad popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day they also visited the Monument to Party Founding.

Libyan Secretary Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Ahmed Amer Al Muakkaf, secretary of the People's Bureau of the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya to the DPRK, arranged a reception Tuesday evening on the occasion of the 6th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 58th anniversary of the WPK.
 Present on invitation were Vice-president Yang Hyong Sop of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and Chairman Ryom Sun Gil of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, Vice-minister Kung Sok Ung of Foreign Affairs and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary in his speech said that the Korean people united close around leader Kim Jong Il have made steady progress in building a great prosperous powerful nation, adding that the friendly relations between Libya and the DPRK have steadily developed under the deep care of the leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop said that the friendly relations between the DPRK and Libya are strong ones as they were provided by President Kim Il Sung and Colonel Gaddafi and are developing under the deep care of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will stand firm on the side of the Libyan Arab people in their energetic efforts to achieve the independent development and prosperity of the country under the leadership of Colonel Gaddafi, he said.    

.

World Public Protests S. Korea's Troop Dispatch Moves 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Organizations of various countries strongly denounced the scheme of the south Korean authorities to dispatch combat troops to Iraq at the request of the U.S.
 The U.S. All Anti-Imperialists Wishing to Build Solidarity with the DPRK in its statement on Sept. 25 said it could hardly repress towering rage at the moves of the south Korean Grand National Party to massively dispatch troops to Iraq in order to plunge south Korea deeper into subjection to the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called upon the international leftist forces and all the people desirous of freedom to unconditionally support the righteous anti-U.S. resistance of the Korean people and the Arab people and demanded that the U.S. administration promptly stop mud-slinging at the DPRK, sign a non-aggression treaty with the DPRK and withdraw its troops from south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the "nuclear issue" of the DPRK is as plain as noonday, the statement stressed that the global community should support the right of the DPRK to build its strong military deterrent without the slightest illusion about the U.S. which killed millions of Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The British Association for the Study of the Songun Policy in letters of protest to the U.S. president and the south Korean leading authority on Sept. 25 strongly protested the moves to send south Korean combat troops to Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day, Alejandro Cao de Benos, chairman of the Association for Friendship with Korean People in Spain, in an open letter to the south Korean people said that the south Korean youth should look forward to a peaceful future of the reunified nation free from the colonial domination of the U.S. and not fall a worthless victim to the U.S. President Bush. 
 Meanwhile, Polish and British personages in protest letters to the U.S. administration and the south Korean authorities condemned the scheme to dispatch troops to Iraq and urged the south Korean people not to support the U.S. criminal acts in Iraq but strive to drive the U.S. troops out of south Korea and achieve Korea's reunification.

KCNA Assails Reckless Remarks of Japan's LDP Heavyweight 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Abe, secretary general of the Liberal Democratic Party of Japan, is busy making unsavory remarks against the DPRK.
 He at a press conference on October 3 asserted that it is necessary to discuss some issues including the revision of the law on the management of foreign exchange in a way to help solve the abduction issue, expressing his intention to examine the economic sanctions to be imposed upon the DPRK, according to Nihonkeizai Shimbun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is improper for a heavyweight of the ruling party to talk about "sanctions" against a sovereign state. He might know this well in view of his present status and his political career deeply involved in the DPRK-Japan relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not the first time that he let loose a string of vituperation against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When he was holding the post as the deputy chief Cabinet secretary, he, referring to the abduction issue, asserted that the early repatriation of all family members of the victims is a precondition for the normalization of the relations." Such stand of the government and the party will remain unchanged in the future too, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He even did not bother to utter such provocative remarks that even if eight members of the families of the abducted Japanese are allowed to visit Japan the curtain of the abduction issue should not be lowered and Japan should not meet any demand for compensation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As far as the abduction issue, which Abe raises as a signboard to win his political popularity, is concerned, it is an issue that has already been solved with the publication of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration as a momentum. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Abe visited Pyongyang at that time as an official member of the Japanese side's delegation. His act of snubbing this can not be construed otherwise than a deliberate act to hamstring the implementation of the declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All facts suffice to prove that Abe is a typical ultra-nationalist who is obsessed with the ambition for militarization and fascistization for reinvasion as he has persistently negated the innumerable crimes Japan committed against Korea, instead of admitting, apologizing and compensating for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Abe should clearly face up to Japan's past history and behave with discretion if he is interested in the political future of Japan and the improved relations between the DPRK and Japan even a bit.

Invincible Workers' Party of Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- October 8 is the 6th anniversary of the election of leader Kim Jong Il as the general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 The People's Army and people of Korea with a high pride are looking back on the victorious course covered by the WPK under the guidance of Kim Jong Il and the immortal exploits performed by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He achieved astonishing feats by leading the Korean revolution in the 1990s when it faced grave trials and difficulties unprecedented in history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK vigorously pushed ahead with the work of imbuing the whole society with the Juche idea, while socialism collapsed in various countries, and thus defended Korean socialism centered on the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il put forward the philosophical principle of the revolution that the army is the Party, state and people, and converted the politics of the WPK into one of regarding the People's Army as the core and the main force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his wise leadership, the WPK has developed and strengthened to be a powerful and seasoned party that leads the Songun revolution to the victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The invincible might of the WPK has been fully displayed in the life and death struggle for defending socialism from the U.S. threat and in the efforts for building a powerful and prosperous nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK has frustrated the persistent moves of the U.S. imperialists to stifle the DPRK by force of arms and safeguarded socialism with credit by waging a powerful anti-U.S. struggle in reliance upon the People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has encouraged the whole Party and the entire people to live and fight with the political and ideological traits and fighting stamina displayed by the People's Army thus paved the way for building a powerful and prosperous nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the guidance of the WPK, the Korean people have built many monumental edifices and modern factories and developed science and technology to make a new advance in the socialist construction as a whole. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The shining victory and success made by the servicemen and people clearly show the correctness of the revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il based on the Songun idea and fully demonstrate the invincibility and leadership ability of the WPK.

Celebrations Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Meetings of agricultural workers and members of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea and workers and members of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea were held on Oct. 6 and 7 to celebrate the 6th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 The meetings heard reports of Chairman Ryom Sun Gil of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea and Chairman Sung Sang Sop of the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea, which were followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporters and speakers said Kim Jong Il's election as general secretary of the WPK was a historic event guaranteeing the vigorous advance of the WPK and the revolution and the eternal prosperity of the motherland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il put forward the unique Songun idea and has strengthened and developed the WPK into a powerful revolutionary party of the Songun era and indicated a bright road of vigorously pushing forward the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, foiling the imperialists' moves to stifle the DPRK, they noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said he has opened a phase of dramatic turn for national reunification, smashing the moves of the anti-reunification forces with the might of Songun, signally heightened the international position of the WPK and the DPRK with his rare far-sightedness and energetic external activities and expanded and strengthened international solidarity for the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon the working people to cherish his Songun idea as their unshaken faith, devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution headed by him in any adversity and remain unboundedly loyal to his idea and leadership.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Election as WPK General Secretary Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il's election as general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea on October 8, Juche 86 (1997) was a historic event that opened a bright prospect of the Party and the revolution, say papers today in editorials dedicated to the day.
 Rodong Sinmun says that his election provided a sure guarantee for strengthening and developing the Party into an eternal Juche-type revolutionary party and accomplishing the Songun revolutionary cause that started on Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that he is a peerless statesman who has led the Korean revolution to victory with his outstanding political ability, the paper goes on: The past six years of his activities are recorded as an immortal epic as he has developed the Party into a strong political organization steering the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a historic feat he has performed for the past 6 years that he has intensified the work to imbue the whole Party and society with the Songun idea as required by the prevailing situation and the new higher stage of the Juche-oriented revolution and consolidated the single-hearted unity of the revolutionary ranks at a new level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the servicepersons and people should become staunch fighters upholding his idea and prestige and self-blasting soldiers defending the security of the headquarters at the risk of their lives and remain true to his Songun idea and leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editorial calls on all the Party members and other working people to actively learn from and thoroughly embody the revolutionary solider spirit based on the spirit of devotedly defending the leader, the do-or-die spirit and the heroic self-sacrificing spirit created and highly displayed by the People's Army, and effect a new surge in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that a bright future is in store for the Korean revolution advancing under the guidance of the Party holding Kim Jong Il in high esteem.

Strengthened Cooperation with UNESCO Stressed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government will further strengthen cooperation with UNESCO and all its member states, true to its foreign policy based on the idea of independence, peace and friendship, to positively contribute to international efforts for world peace, declared the head of the DPRK delegation on October 3, speaking at the 32nd meeting of the General Conference of UNESCO.
 The DPRK in recent years has made enormous efforts to decisively raise the quality of education and the level of up-to-date science and technology to meet the requirements of the era of IT industry in the new century according to its policy of attaching importance to education and science while treasuring and preserving well cultural legacies of the nation and national tradition, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Affirmatively appreciating the activities of UNESCO in the last period under review, he urged the organization to pay due attention in its plan for the new period to finding a more practical and concrete way to ensure fairness and balance in its overall work such as cooperation among its member states and, especially, to increasing the abilities of the developing countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the belief that UNESCO would fulfil its responsibility and role as an intellectual organization in accomplishing the common cause of humankind for peace, development and equality in the new period, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the solution to the nuclear issue between the DPRK and U.S. stands out as a matter of greatest urgency for peace and security of the Korean peninsula, the region and the rest of the world, he said: It is a consistent stand of the DPRK government to settle the nuclear issue peacefully through dialogue and negotiations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government and people will implement the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration to the end to achieve national reconciliation, unity and reunification and contribute to peace and security of the region and the world, he stated.

Seminars Held in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Seminars were held at the Indian International Center, the Romanian Communist Party and the Quito Group for the Study of Man-centered Juche Philosophy of Ecuador on September 30 and October 1 on the occasion of the 6th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 58th anniversary of the WPK.
 Om Prakash Mantri, secretary general of the Asian Regional Committee to Support Korea's Reunification, said at a seminar that the road of victory and glory covered by the WPK bears footmarks of President Kim Il Sung, and the feats made by the WPK and its might and high dignity are unthinkable apart from him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK unswervingly preserves its character and mission as a party defending the demands and interests of the working class and the popular masses and fighting to realize their independence, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Alexandru Pantagi, chairman of the Central Committee of the Romanian Communist Party, at a seminar highly praised  Kim Jong Il who has defended socialism and opened a phase of dramatic turn in accomplishing the cause of the country's reunification by putting forward the original Songun policy embodying the Juche idea to cope with the imperialists' vicious moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK. He said that the WPK is shining as the eternal party of President Kim Il Sung under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 John Moran, executive secretary of the Latin American Institute of the Juche Idea, said at a seminar that the leadership of Kim Jong Il is the source of the invincible might of the WPK. What merits special attention in his leadership is that he has made the Party and the army a harmonious whole and built an invincible party with a mass foundation in which the army and people are united with a single heart by invariably holding fast to the Juche idea as an unwavering guiding idea of the Party, he noted.
